Interface SerDe

All Superinterfaces:
Deserializer, Serializer
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractSerDe, AvroSerDe, BinarySortableSerDe, ByteStreamTypedSerDe, ColumnarSerDe, ColumnarSerDeBase, DelimitedJSONSerDe, DynamicSerDe, LazyBinaryColumnarSerDe, LazyBinarySerDe, LazySimpleSerDe, MetadataTypedColumnsetSerDe, NullStructSerDe, OrcSerde, RegexSerDe, TestSerDe, ThriftByteStreamTypedSerDe, TypedSerDe
Deprecated. 

@Deprecated
public interface SerDe
extends Deserializer, Serializer

A union of HiveDeserializer and HiveSerializer interface. If a developer wants his hive table to be read-only, then he just want to return both readable and writable, then All serdes should extend the abstract class AbstractSerDe, and eventually SerDe interface should be removed
